list-item.p:
All polynomial functions are smooth in

      \mathbb{R}
      ℝ.

They can describe several nonlinear dynamical systems
      (Billings,
      2013), including industrial processes, control systems,
      structural systems, economic and financial systems, biology,
      medicine, and social systems
      (Aguirre,
      2004;
      Billings,
      2013;
      Boynton
      et al., 2018;
      Chiras
      et al., 2001;
      Fung
      et al., 2003;
      Guo
      et al., 2016;
      Kukreja
      et al., 2003;
      W.
      R. Lacerda Junior et al., 2019;
      Martins
      & Aguirre, 2016).
